I fixed `MicroToNanoTreeHelper.toNanoTreeInRange()` so the canonical full-range call (`0.0..1_000_000.0`) now delegates to `toNanoTreeUnfiltered()`. That removes the mismatch where the range path could drop geometry-less nodes, `y == 0` point nodes, or nodes below the hardcoded cutoff.

